{% include accordion title="Check your projects" class="note" icon=true controls=id %}
<div class="accordion_content" id="{{ id }}" markdown='1' hidden>
If you don't know what projects you have available, you can check by running:
```bash
sacctmgr -Pns show user format=account,defaultaccount
```
Or use:
```bash
id $USER | grep "proj"  # check group membership
```
</div>
</div>

{% if include.keep == "true" %}
<div class="highlighted highlighted--basic"><div class="highlighted__body" markdown="1">
To start interactive session or run jobs on compute nodes of either cluster, the jobs need to be associated with a slurm account. 
For users that have access to one or more project directories, their slurm accounts have same names as the project directories. 
The slurm account for **new users** without project directories is called **sandbox**. To specify slurm account, either use: 
- `-A <project_name>` on the slurm command (`srun`, `salloc`, `sbatch`) 
- or add the `#SBATCH -A <project_name>` line to your job script.
</div></div>
{% endif %}